CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Flash Newspicture Magazine, December 13, 1937, p. 26, reads: "Pittsburgh Personalities - Time out for a state senator.  The Honorable Homer Brown, (photo to left), of the Pennsylvania State Legislature, was caught be the candid camera as he lunched between sessions.  Energetic and alert to the interests of his constituents, the Statesman has caused the enactment of laws giving full rights to citizens of his State."
TitMainTitle: Homer S. Brown eating in interior with brick walls and floral chairs
